    <rigor-reason>Data deployment via MCP. No code change. JPS Action row is data (not code) per spec §Executive Summary. STANDARD rigor applies.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>Follow the `jps-action-create` skill. Author + deploy a `sprk_analysisaction` row to spaarkedev1 with `sprk_executoractiontype = 52`, `sprk_actioncode = "SYS-LOOKUP-MEMBERSHIP"`, a JPS-compliant `sprk_systemprompt` (input schema: entityType, roles, identityTypes, includeRelated, limit), an `sprk_outputschemajson` defining the output shape, and `statecode = Active`. Validate via `jps-validate` before deploy. Verify via MCP `read_query` SELECT … WHERE sprk_executoractiontype = 52 returns the row.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS Action-row author with knowledge of the JPS-AUTHORING-GUIDE conventions, upsert-pattern deployment via MCP, and the LookupUserMembership input/output contract.</role>

  <goal>One `sprk_analysisaction` row in spaarkedev1 with sprk_executoractiontype = 52, code SYS-LOOKUP-MEMBERSHIP, statecode Active; canonical JSON source at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/actions/sys-lookup-membership.action.json` committed; `jps-validate` passes; MCP read_query confirms the row.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 FR-1 (lines 109-110) closes the platform-foundations-R3 deployment gap: the C# `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor` shipped in R3 but its corresponding `sprk_analysisaction` row was never deployed to spaarkedev1. Without the row, ActionType 52 cannot be referenced by any playbook (the playbook engine resolves Actions via Dataverse lookup, not C# enum). Owner Q&amp;A confirmed naming convention "SYS-* for system data-ops" (spec line 338). Idempotency via upsert pattern (spec line 343) — if row exists, update; if not, create.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/JPS-AUTHORING-GUIDE.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-034">User-record Membership Resolution Pattern — LookupUserMembership ActionType 52 is the canonical primitive. R4 deploys its missing Action row.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec MUST">MUST follow `jps-action-create` skill; MUST validate each JPS document via `jps-validate` before deployment; MUST use repo JSON files as canonical source-of-truth.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec AC-1">mcp__dataverse__read_query SELECT … FROM sprk_analysisaction WHERE sprk_executoractiontype = 52 returns 1 row.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Upsert pattern (Owner Q&amp;A spec line 343) — if row exists in spaarkedev1, update it; if not, create. Idempotent.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/guides/JPS-AUTHORING-GUIDE.md</file>
